{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "target": "ES2020",
    "module": "commonjs",
    "moduleResolution": "node",
    "esModuleInterop": true,
    "allowSyntheticDefaultImports": true,
    "strict": true,
    "skipLibCheck": true,
    "rootDir": "./src",
    "outDir": "./dist",
    "types": ["node","sequelize"]

  }
   
}

// | Option                                     | Kya karta hai                                           | Simple Example / Reason                                 |
// | ------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------- |
// | **target: "ES2020"**                       | Output JS kis version me convert hoga                   | Latest features allowed (async, optional chaining etc.) |
// | **module: "commonjs"**                     | Node.js ke require() system ko use karega               | Backend projects me commonjs best                       |
// | **moduleResolution: "node"**               | Package resolve Node style se hoga                      | `import xyz from 'abc'` â†’ node_modules me dhundhega     |
// | **resolveJsonModule: true**                | .json files import kar sakte ho                         | `import data from "./data.json"`                        |
// | **esModuleInterop: true**                  | CommonJS aur ES imports ko mix allow                    | `import express from "express"` bina error              |
// | **allowSyntheticDefaultImports: true**     | Default export na ho tab bhi default import chal jayega | Same as above, compatibility                            |
// | **strict: true**                           | TypeScript maximum safety enable                        | Null/undefined errors catch karta h                     |
// | **forceConsistentCasingInFileNames: true** | File name case wrongly use na ho                        | Windows me case-insensitive problems avoid              |
// | **skipLibCheck: true**                     | Node_modules ki type files check skip                   | Build fast, dev smooth                                  |
// | **rootDir: "./src"**                       | TypeScript source folder                                | Sirf src folder compile hoga                            |
// | **outDir: "./dist"**                       | Final JavaScript output folder                          | Compiled JS yahan store hoga                            |
// | **typeRoots**                              | Types definitions kaha se load hongi                    | Custom type files + node types                          |
// | **types: ["node", "sequelize"]**           | Specific types import                                   | Node.js aur Sequelize type support                      |
